====Quotations====

"Sweeney Todd, The Demon Barber of Fleet Street", written by George Dibden Pitt in 1842 for the Britannia Theatre, Hoxton, at Act 3, Scene 2:<br>
JARVIS WILLIAMS (to the Keepers of a madhouse at Peckham): "Stand off you cowardly rascals, or I'll put the 'kiebosh' on the whole consarn."<br>
JONAS: "The 'kiebosh'?"<br>
JARVIS WILLIAMS: "Yes, it's a word of Greek extraction, signifying the upset of the apple-cart - so - bunk!"<br>
JONAS: "Bunk?"<br>
JARVIS WILLIAMS: "Yes, that's another Greek word, and means G.O., go."<br>
